#[global] Unset Universe Checking.

(***********************************************************************************

 Eilenberg-Moore objects

 In this file, we study Eilenberg-Moore objects internal to arbitrary
 bicategories. This generalizes Eilenberg-Moore categories to arbitrary
 bicategories.

 We present three equivalent definitions. The first one expresses Eilenberg-Moore
 objects using universal properties. The second definition coincides with universal
 arrows, and it is remniscent of the work by Street (Formal Theory of Monads) where
 Eilenberg-Moore objects are defined as a right adjoint of the inclusion
 pseudofunctor of `B` into `mnd B`. The third definition is another reformulation
 where Eilenberg-Moore categories are used.

 Contents
 1. Definition via universal properties
 1.1 Cones and morphisms of cones
 1.2 The mapping properties
 1.3 It is a proposition
 2. Definition similar to universal arrows
 2.1 The functor
 2.2 The definition
 2.3 It is a proposition
 3. Equivalence of the first two definitions
 4. Definition via Eilenberg-Moore category
 4.1 The functor
 4.2 The definition
 4.3 It is a proposition
 5. Equivalence to the other two definitions
 6. Bicategories with Eilenberg-Moore objects

 ***********************************************************************************)

Section EMObject.
  Context {B : bicat}
          (m : mnd B).

  (**
   1. Definition via universal properties
   *)

  (**
    1.1 Cones and morphisms of cones
   *)
  Definition em_cone
    : UU
    := ‚àë (x : B), mnd_incl B x --> m.

  Section MakeCone.
    Context (x : B)
            (f : x --> ob_of_mnd m)
            (fm : f ¬∑ endo_of_mnd m ==> id‚ÇÅ x ¬∑ f)
            (fŒ∑ : linvunitor f = rinvunitor f ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ unit_of_mnd m) ‚Ä¢ fm)

                  ‚Ä¢ (fm ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd m)
                  ‚Ä¢ (lunitor f ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd m)
                  ‚Ä¢ fm
                  =
                  (f ‚óÉ mult_of_mnd m)
                  ‚Ä¢ fm).

fm: f ¬∑ endo_of_mnd m ==> id‚ÇÅ x ¬∑ f
fŒ∑: linvunitor f =
(rinvunitor f ‚Ä¢ (f ‚óÉ unit_of_mnd m)) ‚Ä¢ fm
fŒº: ((lassociator f (endo_of_mnd m) (endo_of_mnd m)
  ‚Ä¢ (fm ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd m))
 ‚Ä¢ (lunitor f ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd m)) ‚Ä¢ fm =
(f ‚óÉ mult_of_mnd m) ‚Ä¢ fm
lassociator f (endo_of_mnd m) (endo_of_mnd m)
‚Ä¢ ((fm ‚ñπ endo_of_mnd m)
   ‚Ä¢ (rassociator (id‚ÇÅ x) f (endo_of_mnd m)
      ‚Ä¢ ((id‚ÇÅ x ‚óÉ fm)
         ‚Ä¢ (lassociator (id‚ÇÅ x) (id‚ÇÅ x) f
            ‚Ä¢ (lunitor (id‚ÇÅ x) ‚ñπ f))))) =
(f ‚óÉ mult_of_mnd m) ‚Ä¢ fm

  Coercion em_cone_to_ob (e : em_cone) : B := pr1 e.

  Definition mor_of_em_cone (e : em_cone) : mnd_incl B e --> m := pr2 e.

  Definition em_cone_mor
             (e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ : em_cone)
    : UU
    := ‚àë (g : e‚ÇÅ --> e‚ÇÇ),
       invertible_2cell
         (# (mnd_incl B) g ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÇ)
         (mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÅ).

  Definition make_em_cone_mor
             {e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ : em_cone}
             (g : e‚ÇÅ --> e‚ÇÇ)
             (Œ± : invertible_2cell
                    (# (mnd_incl B) g ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÇ)
                    (mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÅ))
    : em_cone_mor e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ
    := g ,, Œ±.

  Coercion mor_of_em_cone_mor
           {e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ : em_cone}
           (f : em_cone_mor e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ)
    : e‚ÇÅ --> e‚ÇÇ
    := pr1 f.

  Definition cell_of_em_cone_mor
             {e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ : em_cone}
             (f : em_cone_mor e‚ÇÅ e‚ÇÇ)
    : invertible_2cell
        (# (mnd_incl B) f ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÇ)
        (mor_of_em_cone e‚ÇÅ)
    := pr2 f.

  (**
   1.2 The mapping properties
   *)
  Definition em_ump_1
             (e : em_cone)
    : UU
    := ‚àè (q : em_cone), em_cone_mor q e.

  Definition em_ump_2
             (e : em_cone)
    : UU
    := ‚àè (x : B)
         (g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ : x --> e)
         (Œ± : # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÅ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e
              ==>
              # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÇ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e),
      ‚àÉ! (Œ≤ : g‚ÇÅ ==> g‚ÇÇ), ## (mnd_incl B) Œ≤ ‚ñπ _ = Œ±.

  Definition has_em_ump
             (e : em_cone)
    : UU
    := em_ump_1 e √ó em_ump_2 e.

  Section MappingProperties.
    Context {e : em_cone}
            (He : has_em_ump e).

    Definition em_ump_1_mor
               (q : em_cone)
      : q --> e
      := pr1 He q.

    Definition em_ump_1_inv2cell
               (q : em_cone)
      : invertible_2cell
          (# (mnd_incl B) (em_ump_1_mor q) ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e)
          (mor_of_em_cone q)
      := cell_of_em_cone_mor (pr1 He q).

    Definition em_ump_2_cell
               {x : B}
               {g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ : x --> e}
               (Œ± : # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÅ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e
                    ==>
                    # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÇ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e)
      : g‚ÇÅ ==> g‚ÇÇ
      := pr11 (pr2 He x g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ Œ±).

    Definition em_ump_2_eq
               {x : B}
               {g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ : x --> e}
               (Œ± : # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÅ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e
                    ==>
                    # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÇ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e)
      : ## (mnd_incl B) (em_ump_2_cell Œ±) ‚ñπ _ = Œ±
      := pr21 (pr2 He x g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ Œ±).

    
B: bicat
m: mnd B
e: em_cone

g‚ÇÅ, g‚ÇÇ: B ‚ü¶ x, e ‚üß
Œ±: # (mnd_incl B) g‚ÇÅ ¬∑ mor_of_em_cone e ==>

Œ≤‚ÇÅ, Œ≤‚ÇÇ: g‚ÇÅ ==> g‚ÇÇ

Œ≤‚ÇÅ, Œ≤‚ÇÇ: g‚ÇÅ ==> g‚ÇÇ

HŒ≤‚ÇÇ: ## (mnd_incl B) Œ≤‚ÇÇ ‚ñπ mor_of_em_cone e = Œ±
Œ≤‚ÇÅ = Œ≤‚ÇÇ

      exact (maponpaths
               pr1
               (pr1 (isapropifcontr (pr2 He x g‚ÇÅ g‚ÇÇ Œ±) (Œ≤‚ÇÅ ,, HŒ≤‚ÇÅ) (Œ≤‚ÇÇ ,, HŒ≤‚ÇÇ)))).
    Qed.

  (**
   2.1 The functor
   *)
  Section EilenbergMooreFunctor.
    Context (e : em_cone)
            (x : B).

B: bicat
m: mnd B
e: em_cone
x: B
f: B ‚ü¶ x, e ‚üß
?f ¬∑ endo_of_mnd m ==> endo_of_mnd (mnd_incl B x) ¬∑ ?f

      
B: bicat
m: mnd B
e: em_cone
x: B
f: B ‚ü¶ x, e ‚üß
B ‚ü¶ ob_of_mnd (mnd_incl B x), ob_of_mnd m ‚üß
 exact (f ¬∑ mor_of_mnd_mor (mor_of_em_cone e)).
      
B: bicat
m: mnd B
e: em_cone
x: B
f: B ‚ü¶ x, e ‚üß
f ¬∑ mor_of_mnd_mor (mor_of_em_cone e) ¬∑ endo_of_mnd m ==>

  (**
   4.2 The definition
   *)
  Definition is_em_universal_em_cone
             (e : em_cone)
    : UU
    := ‚àè (x : B), adj_equivalence_of_cats (is_em_universal_em_cone_functor e x).

        (hom_to_eilenberg_moore x)

        (hom_to_eilenberg_moore_counit x)) a)
 exact (is_z_iso_hom_to_eilenberg_moore_unit x).

  Defined.

(**
 6. Bicategories with Eilenberg-Moore objects
 *)
Definition bicat_has_em
           (B : bicat)
  : UU
  := ‚àè (m : mnd B),
     ‚àë (e : em_cone m), has_em_ump m e.
